Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed. 01:59 PM Defendant Admir Aganovic in court, in custody, with attorney Eryn M Menden.   Andrew Nesheim appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.
Attorney Menden requests to set bail and gives its arguments.
The State gives its bail recommendation.
The Defendant is unsure as how to proceed.
The Court will set the matter over to the Trial Court.  Hearing scheduled for February 18, 2022 at 10:45 am.

01:50 PM Christian Farina appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Defendant Admir Aganovic in court, in custody.  
Attorney Justin Griffis appears as a friend of the court stating the defendant was not evaluated by the public defender's office, as he was not on the list.  

Defendant acknowledges receipt of complaint, affidavit and supporting warrant and waives reading of documents.  
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties.  
Court advises of right to an attorney.  
Defendant states he would like to have counsel in this matter.  
State requests cash bail in the amount of $10,000.00 and presents arguments.  
Attorney Griffis presents arguments and requests the Court impose a signature bond, or in the alternative if the Court deems cash necessary, that $250.00 be imposed.  

Court denies the defendant bail and the Court reserves the defense right to argue bail at the next date if the defendant qualifies for Public Defender representation.  
Court directs the State to provide the waiver paperwork tomorrow in the event the defendant wishes to waive extradition.  
Public Defenders Office to evaluate the defendant.  
The defendant is remanded to the custody of the Waukesha County Sheriff's Department and the Court sets for a status of counsel date tomorrow.  Hearing scheduled for February 15, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
